aiTopic: Processes Illumina-sequenced ARTIC data by mapping and variant calling, trimming ARTIC primer sequences, identifying primer-binding site mutations, and excluding reads from affected amplicons to calculate allele-frequencies.

The workflow takes a VCF dataset of variants, filters and extracts the variants, generates tabular lists of variants by Samples and by Variant, and creates an overview plot of variants and their allele-frequencies.
Performs read mapping with minimap2, variant calling with medaka, primer trimming with ivar, and variant annotation and filtering for ONT-sequenced ARTIC data.
Performs paired-end read mapping with bwa-mem, followed by sensitive variant calling across a wide range of AFs with lofreq.

Performs single-end read mapping with Bowtie2, followed by deduplication with Picard, realignment with LoFreq, and sensitive variant calling across a wide range of allele frequencies with LoFreq, with final annotation using SnpEff.
Builds a consensus sequence from FILTER PASS variants with intrasample allele-frequency above a configurable consensus threshold, hard-masks regions with low coverage, and removes ambiguous sites.
Trims and maps Illumina SARS-CoV-2 amplicon sequencing data, calls variants, generates a consensus genome, and classifies the samples using Pangolin and Nextclade.
Downloads fastq files for sequencing run accessions provided in a text file using fasterq-dump and creates one job per listed run accession.
Processes the input read files by trimming, aligning, quantifying, and performing quality control analysis on the RNA-seq data.
Executes a viral amplicon/enrichment analysis and intrahost variant calling workflow, including preprocessing, decontamination, assembly, polishing, mapping, variant calling, and coverage analysis.
Runs the nf-core/methylseq pipeline, which performs methylation analysis on sequencing data, including read alignment, deduplication, methylation extraction, and quality control steps.

The workflow starts by converting the input alignments to FASTQ format, aligns the reads to the reference genome using BWA MEM, merges the aligned reads, marks duplicates, sorts the reads, and applies base quality score recalibration to produce the final output BAM file.
Imports the DNA contamination calculation workflow, sets up the TopMed variant caller workflow, creates CRAM index files, calculates DNA contamination, and runs the variant calling process.
The workflow converts VCF files into GDS files, attempts to give unique variant IDs, and optionally checks the GDS files against their VCF inputs.
Performs LD pruning on GDS files, subsets the pruned variants, merges the subsets, and checks the merged GDS file against the inputs.
Generates a null model from phenotype data, performs single variant and aggregate genetic association tests, and summarizes the results.
Performs read length and coverage analysis on input BAM/CRAM files, generates a report, and outputs the results.

Imports various WDL tasks, defines input parameters, checks inputs, aligns reads, merges and sorts BAM files, calculates gene and cell metrics, runs EmptyDrops, and generates the final H5AD output file.
Imports task files, concatenates column content, captures versioning, and outputs the concatenated files and version information.
Converts BAM files to unmapped BAMs, including sorting and outputting the sorted unmapped BAMs.
This notebook analyzes state government tax collections data from the US Census Bureau, visualizes the data using maps, and allows interactive exploration of the data through a widget.
Executes the Seqware-Sanger-Somatic-Workflow, a CWL-based command-line tool for performing somatic variant calling on tumor-normal paired whole-genome sequencing data.
Executes the sort command using a Docker container shared with bamstats to sort input files based on specified keys.
